A few weeks ago with a lot of sadness I saw online that @mccordia passed away. I knew him from very very long time ago. I met him for the first time like 15 years ago at his place in Netherlands. We went from there to a wingsuit camp in Belgium 🇧🇪 then to Cochstedt in Germany 🇩🇪 to organize and film one of the first wingsuit big ways. I was already learning a lot from him about wingsuit flying. After that we met in many different places all over the world, like USA 🇺🇸, Dubai 🇦🇪, Egypt 🇪🇬 and a few other places.
I couldn’t call him a close friend but everytime we met to do some projects together we always had a lot of fun! 
He will be someone who will be really missed in the skydiving community and someone who I will always thanks for his tips about wingsuit flying but also about filmmaking 🎥
This is definitely the shitty part of our sport but I will remember him with a big smile.
Big hug Jarno and see you in the sky ❤️
Photo by: @juanmayerphoto 📸
#wingsuit #talented #restinpeace

Patrick DE GAYARDON: 25 years of legend.
April 13, 1998 - April 13, 2023
This is my post saying BIG THANKS to Patrick for having the vision and idea of creating a new discipline in our sport, wingsuit flying!
Thanks to him we are able today to move forward and even going up in freefall!
I took this photo 16 years ago flying Bird-Man wingsuits in Paraguay - South America, and its still my favorite discipline to film 🎦
Photo by: @juanmayerphoto 📸
#thanks #patrickdegayardon #pioneer #wingsuitflying
